50|$|In simple aircraft, {{without an}} air data {{computer}} or <b>Machmeter,</b> true <b>airspeed</b> can be calculated {{as a function of}} calibrated airspeed and local air density (or static air temperature and pressure altitude, which determine density). Some <b>airspeed</b> <b>indicators</b> incorporate a slide rule mechanism to perform this calculation. Otherwise, it can be performed using this applet or a device such as the E6B (a handheld circular slide rule).|$|R
