50|$|An aircraft’s {{altimeter}} {{is operated}} by the static pressure system. An aircraft’s <b>airspeed</b> <b>indicator</b> is {{operated by the}} static pressure system and the pitot pressure system.|$|R
5000|$|During {{instrument}} flight, the <b>airspeed</b> <b>indicator</b> is used {{in addition}} to the Artificial horizon as an instrument of reference for pitch control during climbs, descents and turns.|$|R
